            <title>[SPARK-13889] Integer overflow when calculating the max number of executor failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-13889</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The max number of executor failure before failing the application is default to twice the maximum number of executors if dynamic allocation is enabled. The default value for &quot;spark.dynamicAllocation.maxExecutors&quot; is Int.MaxValue. So this causes an integer overflow and a wrong result.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
